# Knight Backlog · FULL PLOW LOOP · v0.1.58 → v0.1.59 → v0.1.60 · BP081

Knight — Bishop. This backlog supersedes the prior v0.1.57+v0.1.58 queue. Founder ratified the full Plow Loop priority over Post Results / MCP polish — those slip to v0.1.60 carry-along. Plow Loop is load-bearing: it's what makes the substrate-accumulator architecture demonstrable end-to-end.

**Fire order:**
1. v0.1.57.1 heartbeat/streaming (spec at `BP081_FEATURE_SPEC_ASK_HEARTBEAT_AND_TOKEN_STREAMING.md`) — Founder ratifies separately
2. **v0.1.58 = THIS DOCUMENT, §A** — wait for Founder "v0.1.58 GO"
3. **v0.1.59 = THIS DOCUMENT, §B** — wait for Founder "v0.1.59 GO"
4. **v0.1.60 = THIS DOCUMENT, §C** — wait for Founder "v0.1.60 GO"

Each wave: paste-ready Knight Yoke, 4-5 SEGs (Sonnet 4.6 ALL), VERIFY → STAGING-UPLOAD → SHIP. DRAFT until verified-ratify. Same canonical pattern that landed v0.1.55 → v0.1.57 LATEST.

