# §A — v0.1.58 SCOPE — Shadow E-Giant basic concordance in live Plow loop + R3 Andon persistence

**Theme:** wire the Giant CLASS into the MnemosyneC runtime. Today `iron_egiant_promotion.py` exists as a Shadow-promotion entity but the live TypeScript Plow loop has NO concordance verifier — `TestItOutTab.tsx` uses exact-match grading only. v0.1.58 changes that.

## SEG-1 · Live Giant concordance dispatch into TS Plow loop (P0, **Sonnet 4.6**)

**Goal:** when the Plow loop needs to adjudicate "is this answer verified-correct?" — dispatch a Shadow E-Giant concordance verifier in TypeScript, NOT exact-match string compare.

**Scope:**
- New module: `src/main/plow/giant_concordance.ts`
- Function: `runGiantConcordance(question, candidateAnswer, opts): Promise<{verdict: 'verified' | 'rejected' | 'split', confidence: number, votes: VoterVote[]}>`
- Implementation: dispatch N (default 3) parallel Ollama prompts to local Gemma, each with a different prompt-template (correctness lens / consistency lens / coverage lens — three distinct adversarial framings)
- Parse each verdict (verified / rejected) — Andon discipline: REJECT on uncertainty
- Concordance: 2-of-3 agree → verdict locked; split → escalate (log + flag for manual review)
- Replace exact-match grading in `TestItOutTab.tsx` with this concordance call
- Spider/Sprite accept paths: continue to call `writeVerifiedEblet` ONLY when Giant verdict = `verified`
- Telemetry: log every concordance run with verdict + per-voter votes (for substrate-improvement analysis)

**Edge cases:**
- All 3 voters return same verdict → high-confidence write
- Split 2-1 → write but flag confidence
- Network failure mid-vote → degrade gracefully, log, retry once
- Local Gemma OOM → fallback to single-vote with low confidence flag

**Verify (runtime):**
- Run Test It Out 5 questions on M0 → confirm concordance log entries written
- Confirm verified-correct answers land in eblet store with Giant verdict metadata
- Confirm rejected answers do NOT write (Andon)
- Screenshot Test It Out tab post-run with concordance summary visible

## SEG-2 · R3 Andon cross-session persistence audit + fix (P0, **Sonnet 4.6**)

**Goal:** prove that failed-answer eblets NEVER cache, AND that verified-correct eblets DO persist across Electron restart / app reinstall / OS reboot.

**Reference:** `BP081_SUBSTRATE_ACCUMULATOR_AUDIT.md` SEG-0 R3 gap.

**Scope:**
- Walk every eblet-write path (Spider accept, Sprite delivery winner, Test It Out verified-correct, Ask HOT-write-through)
- Confirm `verified=true` structurally enforced BEFORE write call
- Confirm append-only JSONL is in app userData path that survives reinstall (NOT temp / NOT in-bundle)
- Add startup integrity check: on app launch, scan eblet store for any malformed lines / verified=false survivors → quarantine to `eblets.quarantine.jsonl` + log to diagnostic
- Add "substrate stats" surface (small): Total eblets · Verified-correct count · Last-write timestamp · Quarantine count

**Verify (runtime):**
- Install on M0 · write 3 test eblets via Test It Out · close app · reopen → confirm 3 still present
- Simulate Electron crash mid-write → confirm no partial line · no verified=false survivors
- Screenshot substrate stats surface

## SEG-3 · Stale-message auto-clear on app-version change (P1, **Sonnet 4.6**)

**Founder ratified BP081 2026-06-13 — implement.**

**Goal:** prevent ghost-error rehydration across version upgrades (the BP081 v0.1.57 trap).

**Scope:**
- Stamp app version in localStorage alongside message history: `mnemo_ask_history_version`
- On app launch: read `app.getVersion()`; compare to stamped version
- If different (= upgrade) → prune `mnemo_ask_history` of any entries with error class messages; OR clear entirely; OR keep but mark stale
- Recommend: prune only error-class messages, keep successful Q&A history

**Verify:** simulate v0.1.X → v0.1.X+1 upgrade with seeded error in history → confirm error pruned, valid history kept.

## SEG-4 · Onboarding gate UX auto-flip (P1, **Sonnet 4.6**)

**Founder ratified BP081 2026-06-13 — implement.**

**Goal:** when SKU tier is `full` + Ollama healthy + Gemma present + Test It Out has run at least once, auto-set `mnemosynec_onboarding_complete='1'` so user sees full 17-tab Advanced view.

**Scope:**
- Diagnostic check at app launch
- If all conditions met → set onboarding flag automatically
- Otherwise: keep LeanShell + show "Get Started" affordance with clear progression

**Verify:** install on M2 (pre-existing Gemma) → confirm Advanced view appears post-first-launch without manual flag-setting.

