# Bishop velocity notes for Knight

- **Founder velocity statement: "AS SOON AS POSSIBLE to v0.1.60."** Each version should be a tight, shippable bump — NOT a batched mega-wave. If a SEG in v0.1.58 turns out 3× bigger than estimated, surface it and split to v0.1.58.1 / v0.1.59 instead of bloating the wave.
- **Disk-backed canon (BP080)** binds especially tight at v0.1.59 SEG-2 (per-domain Q banks) and v0.1.60 SEG-2 (Deep Test). Every claim of "14 domains ready" must have 14 disk paths verifiable. No phantom Phase-10-P claims.
- **Belief-vs-binary canon (BP081)** binds at every VERIFY: confirm the SHIPPED binary contains the new feature, not just that source compiled clean.
- **Verify-network-call-fired canon (BP081)** binds at every runtime test: don't trust UI; check the receiver-layer log.
- **v0.1.60 = the moat.** Every prior version is foundation; v0.1.60 is the demonstrable architecture. Treat it with appropriate gravity.

